# Boxel UI Form Input Elements

Boxel UI provides a comprehensive set of form input components for building interactive forms.

## Input

**Import:**
```gts
import { BoxelInput } from '@cardstack/boxel-ui/components';
```

**Purpose:** Standard text input with built-in validation and styling

**Key Props:**
- `@value` - The input value
- `@onInput` - Callback when value changes
- `@placeholder` - Placeholder text
- `@disabled` - Disable the input
- `@invalid` - Show error state
- `@errorMessage` - Error message to display
- `@helperText` - Helper text below input
- `@id` - Input ID for label association

**Usage:**
```gts
<label class="field-label">
  Email
  <BoxelInput
    @type="email"
    @value={{this.email}}
    @onInput={{this.updateEmail}}
    @placeholder="Enter your email"
    @invalid={{this.hasError}}
    @errorMessage="Please enter a valid email"
  />
</label>
```

**Types:**
- `text` (default)
- `email`
- `password`
- `number`
- `url`
- `tel`

## Select

**Import:**
```gts
import { BoxelSelect } from '@cardstack/boxel-ui/components';
```

**Purpose:** Dropdown select with search and custom rendering

**Key Props:**
- `@options` - Array of options to display
- `@selected` - Currently selected option
- `@onChange` - Callback when selection changes
- `@placeholder` - Placeholder text
- `@searchEnabled` - Enable search/filter functionality
- `@disabled` - Disable the select
- `@matchTriggerWidth` - Match dropdown width to trigger

**Basic Usage:**
```gts
<div class="field-group">
  <label>Country</label>
  <BoxelSelect
    @options={{this.countries}}
    @selected={{this.selectedCountry}}
    @onChange={{this.updateCountry}}
    @placeholder="Select a country"
    @searchEnabled={{true}}
  />
</div>
```

**With Custom Rendering:**
```gts
<BoxelSelect
  @options={{this.users}}
  @selected={{this.selectedUser}}
  @onChange={{this.updateUser}}
  @searchEnabled={{true}}
  as |user|
>
  <div class="user-option">
    <Avatar @userId={{user.id}} @displayName={{user.name}} />
    <div>
      <div class="user-name">{{user.name}}</div>
      <div class="user-email">{{user.email}}</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BoxelSelect>
```

## MultiSelect

**Import:**
```gts
import { BoxelMultiSelect } from '@cardstack/boxel-ui/components';
```

**Purpose:** Select multiple options from a list

**Key Props:**
- `@options` - Array of available options
- `@selected` - Array of selected options
- `@onChange` - Callback with new selected array
- `@placeholder` - Placeholder text
- `@searchEnabled` - Enable search
- `@disabled` - Disable the component

**Usage:**
```gts
<div class="field-group">
  <label>Tags</label>
  <BoxelMultiSelect
    @options={{this.availableTags}}
    @selected={{this.selectedTags}}
    @onChange={{this.updateTags}}
    @placeholder="Select tags"
    @searchEnabled={{true}}
  />
</div>
```

**With Custom Chip Display:**
```gts
<BoxelMultiSelect
  @options={{this.categories}}
  @selected={{this.selectedCategories}}
  @onChange={{this.updateCategories}}
  as |category|
>
  <Pill>{{category.name}}</Pill>
</BoxelMultiSelect>
```

## Radio

**Import:**
```gts
import { RadioInput } from '@cardstack/boxel-ui/components';
```

**Purpose:** Radio button group for exclusive selection

**Key Props:**
- `@groupDescription` - Label for the radio group
- `@items` - Array of radio options
- `@name` - Name attribute for the radio group
- `@orientation` - `horizontal` or `vertical` layout
- `@spacing` - Gap between items (e.g., 'default', 'compact')
- `@disabled` - Disable all radio buttons

**Usage:**
```gts
<div class="field-group">
  <label>Subscription Plan</label>
  <RadioInput
    @groupDescription="Choose your plan"
    @items={{this.plans}}
    @name="subscription"
    @orientation="vertical"
    @spacing="default"
  />
</div>
```

**With Custom Layout:**
```gts
{{#each this.paymentMethods as |method|}}
  <label class="radio-option">
    <input
      type="radio"
      name="payment"
      value={{method.id}}
      checked={{eq this.selectedPayment method.id}}
      {{on "change" (fn this.selectPayment method)}}
    />
    <div class="radio-content">
      <strong>{{method.name}}</strong>
      <p>{{method.description}}</p>
    </div>
  </label>
{{/each}}
```

## Switch

**Import:**
```gts
import { BoxelSwitch } from '@cardstack/boxel-ui/components';
```

**Purpose:** Toggle switch for boolean values

**Key Props:**
- `@checked` - Current state (true/false)
- `@onChange` - Callback when toggled
- `@disabled` - Disable the switch

**Usage:**
```gts
<label class="switch-label">
  <BoxelSwitch
    @checked={{this.notificationsEnabled}}
    @onChange={{this.toggleNotifications}}
  />
  <span>Enable notifications</span>
</label>
```

## PhoneInput

**Import:**
```gts
import { PhoneInput } from '@cardstack/boxel-ui/components';
```

**Purpose:** International phone number input with country selector

**Key Props:**
- `@value` - Phone number string
- `@onInput` - Callback when number changes
- `@defaultCountry` - Default country code (e.g., 'US', 'GB')
- `@placeholder` - Placeholder text
- `@disabled` - Disable the input

**Usage:**
```gts
<div class="field-group">
  <label>Phone Number</label>
  <PhoneInput
    @value={{this.phoneNumber}}
    @onInput={{this.updatePhone}}
    @defaultCountry="US"
    @placeholder="(555) 123-4567"
  />
</div>
```

**With Validation:**
```gts
<div class="field-group">
  <label>Contact Number</label>
  <PhoneInput
    @value={{this.phone}}
    @onInput={{this.validatePhone}}
    @invalid={{this.phoneError}}
  />
  {{#if this.phoneError}}
    <span class="error-message">{{this.phoneError}}</span>
  {{/if}}
</div>
```

## DateRangePicker

**Import:**
```gts
import { DateRangePicker } from '@cardstack/boxel-ui/components';
```

**Purpose:** Select a date range with calendar interface

**Key Props:**
- `@startDate` - Start date of range
- `@endDate` - End date of range
- `@onSelect` - Callback with {startDate, endDate}
- `@placeholder` - Placeholder text
- `@disabled` - Disable the picker
- `@minDate` - Minimum selectable date
- `@maxDate` - Maximum selectable date

**Usage:**
```gts
<div class="field-group">
  <label>Event Dates</label>
  <DateRangePicker
    @startDate={{this.eventStart}}
    @endDate={{this.eventEnd}}
    @onSelect={{this.updateDateRange}}
    @placeholder="Select date range"
  />
</div>
```

**With Constraints:**
```gts
<DateRangePicker
  @startDate={{this.bookingStart}}
  @endDate={{this.bookingEnd}}
  @onSelect={{this.updateBooking}}
  @minDate={{this.today}}
  @maxDate={{this.maxBookingDate}}
  @placeholder="Check-in â†’ Check-out"
/>
```

## Complete Form Example

```gts
import { Component } from 'https://cardstack.com/base/card-api';
import { tracked } from '@glimmer/tracking';
import { action } from '@ember/object';
import {
  BoxelInput,
  BoxelSelect,
  BoxelMultiSelect,
  RadioInput,
  BoxelSwitch,
  PhoneInput,
  DateRangePicker,
  Button
} from '@cardstack/boxel-ui/components';

export class UserProfileForm extends Component {
  @tracked name = '';
  @tracked email = '';
  @tracked country = null;
  @tracked interests = [];
  @tracked accountType = 'personal';
  @tracked marketingEmails = false;
  @tracked phone = '';
  @tracked availableFrom = null;
  @tracked availableTo = null;

  countries = [
    { id: 'us', name: 'United States' },
    { id: 'uk', name: 'United Kingdom' },
    { id: 'ca', name: 'Canada' }
  ];

  interestOptions = [
    { id: 'tech', label: 'Technology' },
    { id: 'design', label: 'Design' },
    { id: 'business', label: 'Business' }
  ];

  accountTypes = [
    { id: 'personal', label: 'Personal', description: 'For individual use' },
    { id: 'business', label: 'Business', description: 'For organizations' }
  ];

  @action
  updateName(event: Event) {
    this.name = (event.target as HTMLInputElement).value;
  }

  @action
  updateEmail(event: Event) {
    this.email = (event.target as HTMLInputElement).value;
  }

  @action
  updateCountry(country: any) {
    this.country = country;
  }

  @action
  updateInterests(interests: any[]) {
    this.interests = interests;
  }

  @action
  selectAccountType(type: any) {
    this.accountType = type.id;
  }

  @action
  toggleMarketing() {
    this.marketingEmails = !this.marketingEmails;
  }

  @action
  updatePhone(phone: string) {
    this.phone = phone;
  }

  @action
  updateAvailability({startDate, endDate}: {startDate: Date, endDate: Date}) {
    this.availableFrom = startDate;
    this.availableTo = endDate;
  }

  <template>
    <form class="profile-form">
      <label class="field-label">
        Full Name
        <BoxelInput
          @value={{this.name}}
          @onInput={{this.updateName}}
          @placeholder="John Doe"
        />
      </label>

      <label class="field-label">
        Email
        <BoxelInput
          @type="email"
          @value={{this.email}}
          @onInput={{this.updateEmail}}
          @placeholder="john@example.com"
        />
      </label>

      <div class="field-group">
        <label>Country</label>
        <BoxelSelect
          @options={{this.countries}}
          @selected={{this.country}}
          @onChange={{this.updateCountry}}
          @placeholder="Select your country"
          @searchEnabled={{true}}
        />
      </div>

      <div class="field-group">
        <label>Interests</label>
        <BoxelMultiSelect
          @options={{this.interestOptions}}
          @selected={{this.interests}}
          @onChange={{this.updateInterests}}
          @placeholder="Select your interests"
        />
      </div>

      <div class="field-group">
        <label>Account Type</label>
        <RadioInput
          @groupDescription="Choose account type"
          @items={{this.accountTypes}}
          @name="accountType"
          @orientation="vertical"
        />
      </div>

      <div class="field-group">
        <label>Phone Number</label>
        <PhoneInput
          @value={{this.phone}}
          @onInput={{this.updatePhone}}
          @defaultCountry="US"
        />
      </div>

      <div class="field-group">
        <label>Availability Period</label>
        <DateRangePicker
          @startDate={{this.availableFrom}}
          @endDate={{this.availableTo}}
          @onSelect={{this.updateAvailability}}
          @placeholder="Select date range"
        />
      </div>

      <label class="switch-container">
        <BoxelSwitch
          @checked={{this.marketingEmails}}
          @onChange={{this.toggleMarketing}}
        />
        <span>Receive marketing emails</span>
      </label>

      <div class="form-actions">
        <Button @kind="primary" type="submit">
          Save Profile
        </Button>
        <Button @kind="secondary" type="button">
          Cancel
        </Button>
      </div>
    </form>

    <style scoped>
      .profile-form {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 1.5rem;
        max-width: 600px;
        padding: 2rem;
      }

      .field-label {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 0.5rem;
        font-weight: 500;
      }

      .field-group {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 0.5rem;
      }

      .field-group label {
        font-weight: 500;
      }

      .switch-container {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 0.75rem;
        cursor: pointer;
      }

      .form-actions {
        display: flex;
        gap: 0.75rem;
        justify-content: flex-end;
        margin-top: 1rem;
        padding-top: 1rem;
        border-top: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
      }
    </style>
  </template>
}
```

## Best Practices

1. **Enable search for long lists** - Use `@searchEnabled` on Select/MultiSelect
2. **Provide helpful placeholder text** - Guide users on expected input
3. **Show validation errors** - Use `@invalid` and `@errorMessage` props
4. **Handle loading states** - Disable inputs during form submission
5. **Use appropriate input types** - email, tel, url for better mobile keyboards
6. **Consider accessibility** - Proper labels, ARIA attributes, keyboard navigation
7. **Group related fields** - Use fieldsets or visual grouping
8. **Provide clear feedback** - Show success/error messages after actions
9. **Test on mobile** - Ensure touch targets are adequate (min 44px)
